SIMPLE: subtly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subtly
<hw>Sub"tly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a subtle manner;
slyly; artfully; cunningly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou seest how <qex>subtly</qex> to detain thee I devise.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nicely; delicately.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the nice bee what sense so <qex>subtly</qex> true.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Subtly</qex> communicating itself to my sensibilities, but
evading the analysis of my mind.</q> <rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Deceitfully; delusively.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subtonic</ent>⟦br⟧
